        "---",
        "",
        "# Part 1: Theory & Background",
        "",
        "## \ud83e\udd14 What is Sentiment Analysis?",
        "",
        "**Sentiment Analysis** (also called **opinion mining**) is the computational study of emotions, attitudes, and opinions expressed in text.",
        "",
        "### Real-World Applications",
        "",
        "| Domain | Application | Example |",
        "|--------|-------------|---------|",
        "| **Business** | Customer feedback | \"This product is amazing!\" \u2192 Positive |",
        "| **Social Media** | Brand monitoring | Tweet sentiment about new iPhone |",
        "| **Politics** | Public opinion | Sentiment towards policy changes |",
        "| **Literature** | Narrative analysis | Emotional arc of Romeo & Juliet |",
        "| **Healthcare** | Patient feedback | Satisfaction with treatment |",
        "| **Finance** | Market sentiment | News sentiment predicting stock prices |",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "## \ud83d\udd0d Why Analyze Literary Sentiment?",
        "",
        "### Quantitative Literary Analysis",
        "",
        "Traditional literary criticism is **qualitative**:",
        "- Close reading of passages",
        "- Thematic interpretation",
        "- Subjective expert opinions",
        "",
        "Sentiment analysis adds **quantitative rigor**:",
        "- Measure emotional intensity objectively",
        "- Compare narrative structures across genres",
        "- Identify patterns invisible to human readers",
        "- Scale analysis to thousands of texts",
        "",
        "### Example: The Hero's Journey",
        "",
        "Joseph Campbell's **monomyth** describes a universal narrative pattern:",
        "",
        "```",
        "Ordinary \u2192 Call to \u2192 Refusal \u2192 Meeting \u2192 Crossing \u2192 Tests \u2192 Climax \u2192 Return",
        "World     Adventure             Mentor   Threshold",
        "  \ud83d\ude10   \u2192    \ud83d\ude03    \u2192    \ud83d\ude30   \u2192    \ud83d\ude0a   \u2192    \ud83d\ude28    \u2192   \ud83d\ude30  \u2192   \ud83d\ude31   \u2192   \ud83c\udf89",
        "```",
        "",
        "Sentiment analysis can **objectively detect** these patterns!",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "## \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Three Approaches to Sentiment Analysis",
        "",
        "### 1. \ud83d\udcd6 Lexicon-Based (Symbolic)",
        "",
        "**Core Idea:** Use dictionary of pre-labeled words",
        "",
        "**How it Works:**",
        "```python",
        "# Simplified lexicon",
        "lexicon = {",
        "    \"love\": +0.7,",
        "    \"hate\": -0.8,",
        "    \"happy\": +0.6,",
        "    \"sad\": -0.5,",
        "    \"very\": 1.5x,  # Amplifier",
        "    \"not\": -1.0x   # Negator",
        "}",
        "",
        "# Analyze: \"I am very happy\"",
        "score = lexicon[\"very\"] * lexicon[\"happy\"] = 1.5 * 0.6 = +0.9",
        "",
        "# Analyze: \"I am not happy\"  ",
        "score = lexicon[\"not\"] * lexicon[\"happy\"] = -1.0 * 0.6 = -0.6",
        "```",
        "",
        "**Examples:**",
        "- **VADER:** Optimized for social media (handles emojis, ALL CAPS, !!!)",
        "- **TextBlob:** General-purpose, simple API",
        "- **SyuzhetR:** Specifically designed for literary narratives",
        "- **SentimentR:** Advanced valence shifter detection",
        "",
        "**Pros:**",
        "- \u2705 Fast (1000s of sentences/second)",
        "- \u2705 Interpretable (can see why score is X)",
        "- \u2705 No training data needed",
        "- \u2705 Works out-of-the-box",
        "",
        "**Cons:**",
        "- \u274c Misses context (\"not bad\" = positive)",
        "- \u274c Limited vocabulary",
        "- \u274c Sarcasm blind (\"Oh great, another rainy day\")",
        "- \u274c Fixed rules can't adapt",
        "",
        "**Best For:**",
        "- Quick exploratory analysis",
        "- When interpretability matters",
        "- Resource-constrained environments",
        "- General domains (not highly specialized)",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "### 2. \ud83d\udcca Statistical Machine Learning",
        "",
        "**Core Idea:** Learn patterns from labeled training data",
        "",
        "**How it Works:**",
        "```python",
        "# Training Phase",
        "training_data = [",
        "    (\"I loved it!\", positive),",
        "    (\"Terrible movie\", negative),",
        "    (\"It was okay\", neutral),",
        "    # ... 10,000 more examples",
        "]",
        "",
        "# Extract features",
        "features = count_words(training_data)",
        "# \"loved\": appears 80% in positive, 5% in negative \u2192 strong positive signal",
        "",
        "# Build classifier",
        "model = train_naive_bayes(features, labels)",
        "",
        "# Prediction Phase",
        "new_text = \"I loved the ending!\"",
        "features = count_words(new_text)  # \"loved\" detected",
        "prediction = model.predict(features)  # \u2192 positive (90% confidence)",
        "```",
        "",
        "**Examples:**",
        "- **Naive Bayes:** Simple probabilistic classifier",
        "- **Support Vector Machines (SVM):** Find optimal decision boundary",
        "- **Logistic Regression:** Probability-based classification",
        "",
        "**Pros:**",
        "- \u2705 Can learn domain-specific patterns",
        "- \u2705 Faster than deep learning",
        "- \u2705 Good with sufficient training data",
        "- \u2705 Transparent decision boundaries",
        "",
        "**Cons:**",
        "- \u274c Requires labeled training data (expensive)",
        "- \u274c Feature engineering needed",
        "- \u274c Loses word order (\"not happy\" = \"happy not\")",
        "- \u274c Limited context window",
        "",
        "**Best For:**",
        "- Domain-specific applications with training data",
        "- When you need faster-than-transformers speed",
        "- When you have computational constraints",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "### 3. \ud83e\udde0 Deep Learning (Transformers)",
        "",
        "**Core Idea:** Learn rich representations from massive text corpora",
        "",
        "**How it Works:**",
        "```",
        "Input: \"I did not love the movie\"",
        "",
        "Step 1: Tokenization",
        "[\"I\", \"did\", \"not\", \"love\", \"the\", \"movie\"] \u2192 [101, 1045, 2134, 2025, 2293, 1996, 3185, 102]",
        "",
        "Step 2: Contextual Embeddings (BERT magic)",
        "Each word gets 768-dimensional vector that captures:",
        "- Word meaning",
        "- Context (what words surround it)",
        "- Syntax (grammar role)",
        "- Semantic relationships",
        "",
        "\"love\" with \"not\" before it \u2192 different encoding than \"love\" alone",
        "",
        "Step 3: Attention Mechanism",
        "Model learns to focus on important words:",
        "- \"not\" gets high attention (modifier)",
        "- \"love\" gets high attention (main sentiment word)",
        "- \"the\" gets low attention (unimportant)",
        "",
        "Step 4: Classification",
        "[CLS] token representation \u2192 Neural Network \u2192 Probability distribution",
        "{positive: 0.05, neutral: 0.15, negative: 0.80} \u2192 negative",
        "```",
        "",
        "**Examples:**",
        "- **BERT:** Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers",
        "- **RoBERTa:** Robustly Optimized BERT (better trained)",
        "- **DistilBERT:** Distilled (smaller, faster) version of BERT",
        "- **GPT variants:** Generative Pre-trained Transformers",
        "",
        "**Pros:**",
        "- \u2705 State-of-the-art accuracy",
        "- \u2705 Understands context deeply",
        "- \u2705 Handles negation, sarcasm better",
        "- \u2705 Transfer learning (pre-trained on billions of words)",
        "- \u2705 Captures long-range dependencies",
        "",
        "**Cons:**",
        "- \u274c Computationally expensive (needs GPU)",
        "- \u274c Slow (seconds per sentence vs milliseconds)",
        "- \u274c \"Black box\" - hard to interpret",
        "- \u274c May overfit on small datasets",
        "- \u274c Large model sizes (GB of storage)",
        "",
        "**Best For:**",
        "- When accuracy is paramount",
        "- Sufficient computational resources",
        "- Complex, nuanced text",
        "- Multiple languages/domains",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "## \ud83c\udfad Comparison Example: \"not bad\"",
        "",
        "Let's see how each approach handles negation:",
        "",
        "**Text:** \"The movie was not bad.\"",
        "",
        "### VADER (Lexicon):",
        "```python",
        "# \"not\" = negator",
        "# \"bad\" = -0.5",
        "# Result: -1.0 * -0.5 = +0.5 (positive) \u2705 Correct!",
        "```",
        "**Verdict:** \u2705 VADER handles simple negation well",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "### Naive Bayes (Statistical ML):",
        "```python",
        "# Bag of words: [\"movie\", \"was\", \"not\", \"bad\"]",
        "# P(positive | \"not\") = 0.3",
        "# P(positive | \"bad\") = 0.1",
        "# P(positive | \"not bad\") = ??? (doesn't know phrase)",
        "# Result: Negative \u274c Wrong!",
        "```",
        "**Verdict:** \u274c Basic ML struggles with negation",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "### RoBERTa (Transformer):",
        "```python",
        "# Contextual encoding:",
        "# \"not\" attending to \"bad\" \u2192 modifier relationship detected",
        "# Combined representation \u2192 positive sentiment",
        "# Result: Positive (87% confidence) \u2705 Correct!",
        "```",
        "**Verdict:** \u2705 Transformers excel at context",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "## \ud83e\udd1d Why Use an Ensemble?",
        "",
        "**The Wisdom of Crowds:** Combining multiple models often beats any single model.",
        "",
        "### Model Strengths/Weaknesses",
        "",
        "| Model | Literary Text | Social Media | Negation | Sarcasm | Speed |",
        "|-------|---------------|--------------|----------|---------|-------|",
        "| **VADER** | \u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50 | \ud83d\ude80\ud83d\ude80\ud83d\ude80 |",
        "| **TextBlob** | \u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50 | \ud83d\ude80\ud83d\ude80\ud83d\ude80 |",
        "| **SyuzhetR** | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50 | \ud83d\ude80\ud83d\ude80 |",
        "| **RoBERTa** | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \ud83d\ude80 |",
        "| **DistilBERT** | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50 | \ud83d\ude80\ud83d\ude80 |",
        "",
        "### Ensemble Strategies",
        "",
        "#### 1. Simple Average",
        "```python",
        "ensemble_score = (vader + textblob + roberta) / 3",
        "```",
        "**Pros:** Simple, reduces individual model bias  ",
        "**Cons:** Treats all models equally",
        "",
        "#### 2. Weighted Average",
        "```python",
        "ensemble_score = (0.2 * vader + 0.3 * syuzhetr + 0.5 * roberta)",
        "```",
        "**Pros:** Emphasizes more accurate models  ",
        "**Cons:** Need validation data to determine weights",
        "",
        "#### 3. Majority Vote",
        "```python",
        "predictions = [vader_pred, textblob_pred, roberta_pred]",
        "ensemble_pred = most_common(predictions)",
        "```",
        "**Pros:** Robust to outlier models  ",
        "**Cons:** Loses nuance (only for classification)",
        "",
        "#### 4. Stacking",
        "```python",
        "# Train meta-model on individual model outputs",
        "meta_model = LogisticRegression()",
        "meta_model.fit(",
        "    [[vader, textblob, roberta], ...],  # Features",
        "    [true_label, ...]                     # Labels",
        ")",
        "```",
        "**Pros:** Can learn complex model interactions  ",
        "**Cons:** Requires labeled data",
        "",
